# Frontend Conventions

- Vite + React 19, plain JSX (no TypeScript). Functional components only.
- `vite.config.js` sets `build.outDir: 'build'` — do not change; the deployment
  flow uploads `frontend/build/` to the server html directory.
- Dev server proxies `/api` to `http://localhost:5000` (Express backend).
- ALL site copy/content lives in `src/data/siteContent.js`. Components should
  render from that data — never hard-code business content (names, prices,
  schedules, links) inside components.
- One component per page section in `src/components/`, each importing its own
  co-located CSS file. Page assembly happens in `App.jsx`.
- Linting: `npm run lint` (oxlint).
- Reviews currently persist to localStorage (`agoge-reviews` key) and the contact
  form falls back to mailto. Both have TODOs to switch to `/api/reviews` and
  `/api/contact` when the backend is wired up.
